President Trump provided an update on Hurricane Dorian, stating that Florida was fortunate to have been grazed by the storm, but South Carolina and North Carolina may still be affected. He mentioned that the United States Coast Guard is assisting with relief efforts in the Bahamas, which was hit hard by the hurricane. The President also discussed the preparations in place to help farmers in the event of devastation to farmland, and he reiterated the administration's stance on not doing business with Huawei. He also addressed the possibility of a meeting with Iranian President Rouhani and expressed his confidence in Boris Johnson's ability to handle Brexit. The President also mentioned the rollback of regulations on energy-efficient lightbulbs and discussed efforts to combat the opioid crisis.